<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-7">
    <div class="row">

      <!-- header line -->
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <button type="button" class="pull-right btn btn-danger btn-lg navigation" ng-click="exit()">
          Cancel
        </button>  
        <h3 class="wizard-title">
          Print Bed Leveling
        </h3>
        <br/>&nbsp;
      </div>

      <!-- text contents step 1 -->
      <div class="col-md-12" ng-show="step == '1'">
        <p>The following steps will guide you through the process of leveling the
          print bed. This is necessary to achieve best print results and lay down a perfect
          first layer that bonds firmly to the print surface.</p>
        <p>Please confirm:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>A clean printbed is installed.</li>
          <li>The nozzle <span ng-if="isDualExtruder">tips are</span><span ng-if="!isDualExtruder">tip is</span> cleaned from any print material residue
            (gently remove any material with tweezers).</li>
          <li>No Filament is loaded in the extruder that you do not level the print bed with in the first place.</li>        
        </ul>
        <button type="button" class="pull-right btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step2()">
          OK, continue
        </button>     
      </div>

      <!-- text contents step 2 -->
      <div class="col-md-12" ng-show="step == '2'">
        <p ng-show="noPreheatingProfileSelected"><b>Error: No preheating profile is configured.</b> Check [Configuration] tab first!</p>
        <p ng-show="!noPreheatingProfileSelected">Please wait while the print bed is beeing preheated. This may take a couple of minutes.</p>
        <p ng-show="!noPreheatingProfileSelected">Current/ Target print bed temperature: <b>{{ bed_temp }} / {{ temp.bed.target }} Â°C</b></p>
        <br/>
        <br/>  
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step1()">
          Back
        </button>            
      </div>

      <!-- text contents step 21 -->
      <div class="col-md-12" ng-show="step == '21'">
        <p>Select the extruder used as height reference for leveling the print bed:</p>
        <div class="btn-group text-center">
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" ng-model="extruder" btn-radio="'left_extruder'">Left</button>
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" ng-model="extruder" btn-radio="'right_extruder'">Right</button>
        </div>
        <br/>
        <br/>
        <br/>  
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step2()">
          Back
        </button>         
        <button ng-show="(extruder == 'left_extruder') || (extruder == 'right_extruder')" type="button" class="pull-right btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step3()">
          Next
        </button>    
      </div>

      <!-- text contents step 3 -->
      <div class="col-md-12" ng-show="step == '3'"> 
        <p>Now loosen the two set screws on the <b>{{ secondary_extruder_name }}</b> extruder barrel.</p>
        <p><b>ATTENTION: Carefully check if extruder is still hot before touching the nozzle!.</b></p>
        <p>Then slide the {{ secondary_extruder_name }} extruder barrel up to make sure the {{ secondary_extruder_name }} nozzle tip is a bit higher 
          than the {{ primary_extruder_name }} tip.</p>    
        <br/>
        <br/>    
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step2()">
          Back
        </button>         
        <button type="button" class="pull-right btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step5()">
          Next
        </button>     
      </div>

      <!-- text contents step 5 -->
      <div class="col-md-12" ng-show="step == '5'">
        <h4>Position 1:</h4>
        <p>Loosen the print bed leveling thumb screw on the <b>front</b>.
        <p>The print bed must be able to easily pivot up and down against the spring suspension of the front
        leveling mechanism. Next, move the print bed up against the print head:</p>
        <p>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="move_up()">
          Move Print Bed up
        </button>         
        </p>
        <p>After the movement gently refasten the bed leveling thumb screw.</p>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step3()">
          Back
        </button>         
        <button type="button" class="pull-right btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step6()">
          Next
        </button>     
      </div>      

      <!-- text contents step 6 -->
      <div class="col-md-12" ng-show="step == '6'">
        <h4>Position 2:</h4>
        <p>Loosen the print bed leveling thumb screw on the <b>right</b>.
        <p>The print bed must be able to easily pivot up and down against the spring suspension of the front
        leveling mechanism. Next, move the print bed up against the print head:</p>
        <p>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="move_up()">
          Move Print Bed up
        </button>         
        </p>
        <p>After the movement gently refasten the bed leveling thumb screw.</p>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step5()">
          Back
        </button>         
        <button type="button" class="pull-right btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step7()">
          Next
        </button>     
      </div>      

      <!-- text contents step 7 -->
      <div class="col-md-12" ng-show="step == '7'">
        <h4>Position 3:</h4>
        <p>Loosen the print bed leveling thumb screw on the <b>left</b>.
        <p>The print bed must be able to easily pivot up and down against the spring suspension of the front
        leveling mechanism. Next, move the print bed up against the print head:</p>
        <p>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="move_up()">
          Move Print Bed up
        </button>         
        </p>
        <p>After the movement gently refasten the bed leveling thumb screw.</p>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step6()">
          Back
        </button>         
        <button ng-if="isDualExtruder" type="button" class="pull-right btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step9()">
          Next
        </button>
        <button ng-if="!isDualExtruder" type="button" class="pull-right btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="exit()">
          Done!
        </button>     
      </div>

      <!-- text contents step 9 -->
      <div class="col-md-12" ng-show="step == '9'">
        <p>The print bed is leveled now.</p>
        <p>Finally, slide the <b>{{ secondary_extruder_name }}</b> extruder barrel back down until it just
          touches the print bed and gently tighten the two set screws again.</p>
        <p>That's it, you are done.</p>
        <br/>
        <br/>  
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step7()">
          Back
        </button>         
        <button type="button" class="pull-right btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="exit()">
          Done!
        </button>     
      </div> 

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- image step 1 -->
  <div class="col-md-5" ng-show="step == '1'">
    <!-- picture: cleaning nozzle with tweezers -->
    <img src="<%= asset_path("touchapp/images/wizard_leveling_tweezers.jpg") %>" class="img-responsive wizard-image">
  </div>  

  <!-- image step 2 -->
  <div class="col-md-5" ng-show="step == '2'">
    <!-- picture: printbed in preheat-position -->
    <img src="<%= asset_path("touchapp/images/wizard_leveling_preheat.jpg") %>" class="img-responsive wizard-image">    
  </div> 

  <!-- image step 21 -->
  <div class="col-md-5" ng-show="step == '21'">
    <!-- picture: printbed in preheat-position -->
    <img src="<%= asset_path("touchapp/images/wizard_leveling_preheat.jpg") %>" class="img-responsive wizard-image">    
  </div> 

  <!-- image step 3 -->
  <div class="col-md-5" ng-show="step == '3'">
    <!-- picture: barrel set screws-->
    <img src="<%= asset_path("touchapp/images/wizard_leveling_nozzleup.jpg") %>" class="img-responsive wizard-image">    
  </div>   

  <!-- image step 5 -->
  <div class="col-md-5" ng-show="step == '5'">
    <!-- picture: fasten front thumbscrew -->
    <img src="<%= asset_path("touchapp/images/wizard_leveling_pos1.jpg") %>" class="img-responsive wizard-image">
  </div>   

  <!-- image step 6 -->
  <div class="col-md-5" ng-show="step == '6'">
    <!-- picture: fasten right thumbscrew -->
    <img src="<%= asset_path("touchapp/images/wizard_leveling_pos2.jpg") %>" class="img-responsive wizard-image">
  </div>   

  <!-- image step 7 -->
  <div class="col-md-5" ng-show="step == '7'">
    <!-- picture: fasten left thumbscrew -->
    <img src="<%= asset_path("touchapp/images/wizard_leveling_pos3.jpg") %>" class="img-responsive wizard-image">
  </div>

  <!-- image step 9 -->
  <div class="col-md-5" ng-show="step == '9'">
    <!-- picture: fasten barrel -->
    <img src="<%= asset_path("touchapp/images/wizard_leveling_nozzledown.jpg") %>" class="img-responsive wizard-image">
  </div> 

</div>
